tweet: I'm afraid that's the end of #fireweed week folks. I hope you've enjoyed it. There'll be a brand new species tomorrow.

name: Species of UK
tweet: #Fireweed flowers have four magenta to pink petals, 2 to 3 cm in diameter. The styles have four stigmas.

name: Species of UK
tweet: #Fireweed leaves in autumn. (via  http://t.co/Af2E7rtRlP)  http://t.co/C2QvJteYIG

name: Species of UK
tweet: This unique leaf structure is the surest way of identifying #fireweed in its earlier stages of growth.

name: Species of UK
tweet: The leaves of #fireweed are quite unique. The veins do not terminate at the edge of the leaf, but circle back and join together.

name: Species of UK
tweet: The #fireweed species name 'angustifolium' is a composite of angustus and folium meaning 'narrow-leaved.'

name: Species of UK
tweet: #Fireweed is a member of the Onagraceae family, the willowherbs, evening primroses and fushcias.

name: Species of UK
tweet: If you Google rosebay willowherb there's about a 50/50 split between nature sites celebrating it & gardening sites condemning it. #fireweed

name: Species of UK
tweet: Unfortunately #fireweed has become a victim of its own success and is now commonly regarded as a weed :( shame for such a beautiful flower!

name: Species of UK
tweet: Their parachutes allow #fireweed seeds to disperse easily even on a light breeze, another reason for the plant's success as a coloniser.

name: Species of UK
tweet: Another image I love. The architecture of #fireweed seed pods. (via  http://t.co/1JouwOyiPl)  http://t.co/8XHbX9FwhZ

name: Species of UK
tweet: #Fireweed seed pods opening up. (pic via  http://t.co/K0QxDMZkwr)  http://t.co/MMufvWcjg2

name: Species of UK
tweet: Once pollinated a #fireweed flower produces seed pods that can hold between 300-600 seeds. The seeds produce a tuft of hair (parachute).

name: Species of UK
tweet: One of the reasons for the success of #fireweed is that it has fine shallow rhizome root systems that can colonise new areas quickly.

name: BeguzWhyNot
tweet: Hula hands. #fireweed

name: Species of UK
tweet: Have a look at this fabulous short BBC video about #fireweed:  http://t.co/lwtK57L50h

name: Species of UK
tweet: Other local names for #fireweed (that I can't explain) are blood-vine, cat‚Äôs eyes, red buffer, and ramping molly.

name: Species of UK
tweet: Following its success in London, #fireweed also became known as 'London pride' and 'London‚Äôs ruin.' It is London's official county flower.

name: Species of UK
tweet: #Fireweed leaves resemble some willows. This has led to names such as blooming sally (Cumberland), or flowering withy (Berkshire).

name: Species of UK
tweet: In folklore #fireweed should not be picked, otherwise a thunderstorm will ensue. This led to another dramatic name, 'thunder-flower.'

name: Species of UK
tweet: A name once quite widely used for #fireweed was 'French willow.' I can't track down the origin of this one. Does anybody know?

name: Species of UK
tweet: In Clydebank during the war, #fireweed sprung up in the ruins of the Singer Sewing Machine factory, leading to the local name 'singerweed.'

name: Species of UK
tweet: We've looked at why rosebay willowherb gets called #fireweed or bombweed. Here are a few of its other names....

tweet: #Fireweed leaves are lance-like arranged spirally up its stem. (pic via  http://t.co/NEMBgCPP0U)  http://t.co/zZIKpBW3QE

name: Species of UK
tweet: Burnt ground from the war = ideal conditions for rosebay willowherb to thrive & it become known locally as 'bombweed' as well as #fireweed.

name: Species of UK
tweet: It used to be a scarce woodland plant, but has colonised cleared areas created by human activity and it's now extremely common. #fireweed

tweet: Classic view of #fireweed, rosebay willowherb. (via  http://t.co/YcVQ3VuGH1)  http://t.co/bQPKzYyFV4

name: Species of UK
tweet: #Fireweed is recognisable from its tall, pink flower spikes crowding in thick stands in open spaces like verges and waste ground.
